<font color="#FF0000">ITS NOT JUST WIVES!</font><br>
<tt>Thu Dec 19  2:01:35 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
I was a nurse at Bien Hoa in 1970.  I was supposed to get married to Captain Brooke Rowe when we got back to the states.<br><br>
On February 8, 1970, Brooke left for home.<br><br>
12 days later I got a letter from him saying he married his high school sweetheart on Valentine's Day.<br><br>
I stayed in Vietnam until April of 1972.<br><br>
Just married a fine man (our first) who is an author here in Gardena, California.  But for 23 years I was so very very bitter.<br><br>
Brenda Salinger<br>
Capt, ANC
